15 killed, 11 injured in Zamboanga City fire
Zamboanga City (CNN Philippines) — Fifteen people were killed while 11 others were injured in a fire that struck the Zamboanga City Public Market at dawn on Saturday (October 31).
According to police sources, the fatalities – some of whom were minors – were trapped in the market.
The fire reportedly started at a structure known as Row G and spread until it reached a wooden structure along Magay Street where ukay-ukay (secondhand) clothes were sold.
